I like this little pistol (as is obvious by the ~$800 I've put in it). I just never seem to find occasion to carry it. I like my 1911 more and my wife says I don't need a dedicated "bathroom gun".

(NOTE: It hasn't actually been in the bathroom. That's what my Shield9 is for.)

This is a BG380 at heart and is not a "fun range toy" or for gunfighting. The trigger is stiff by design, but breaks very cleanly and has a very obvious "take-up" before the break, allowing precision shots with a little practice. The laser makes for great dry-fire practice.

Cold Hammer Forging of barrels has been known for decades to produce the most accurate, longest lasting rifle barrels obtainable. The Cold Hammer Forging of barrels is accomplished through intense hydraulic pressure applied at opposing angles by carbide steel hammers. During the hammering process, a mandrel is inserted into the bore while the carbide steel hammers shape the barrel around the mandrel creating the chamber, the lands, and the grooves. In addition to the aforementioned benefits, the Cold Hammer Forging process creates a defect free bore and the most consistent chamber possible.

I am looking to upgrade to a Ruger Super Blackhawk Talo or Ruger Alaskan in .44mag so I can use the same ammo in all my .44mags.  Right now I use Buffalo Bore’s 340+p+ .44 mag round (1250fps out of an Alaskan) and the S&W is not rated for safe use along with the cylinder being too short for the round to fit. My S&W comes with the factory case w/ accessories (fired casing, I think I have the manuals also- will look), a black De Santis leather holster and Crimson Trace Laser Grips. BUFFALO-BARNES LEAD-FREE Premium 35 Whelen Supercharged 225 gr. TSX (2800 fps) - 20 Round Box

Again, as per customer request, Buffalo Bore has developed two new 35 Whelen loads. Item 42A features a Sierra 225gr. SPTZ-BT bullet @ 2705 fps out of my Remington 700. (24 inch bbl)  At the expected impact velocities, this bullet will mushroom readily, but hold together on large game like bull elk. We recommend this load for use on smallish big game (like whitetail deer) through Yukon Moose and Bison. However, on very tough (other than broadside) angling shots on large big game, we recommend the use of our item 42B, which features a 225gr. Barnes TSX bullet @ 2654 fps out of the same rifle. The TSX load is a bit slower than the Sierra load because the long-for-weight all copper TSX uses up more case/powder capacity than the shorter Sierra bullet of the same weight.

If you desire the deepest possible penetration from an expanding bullet in 35 Whelen, the 225gr. Barnes TSX bullet delivers. It will out penetrate a 250gr. typical premium partition bullet, but gives the advantage of higher velocity, flatter trajectory and reduced recoil of the lighter 225gr. bullet. You can use this TSX load for bad angle (quartering or going straight away) shots on the largest North American big game.

This ammo is designed to be the highest quality, most powerful/versatile, 35 Whelen ammo, in the world. It exhibits sub MOA accuracy in our test rifle.
